WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.599
2 Corinthians chapter number 9, and we'll be looking here at the entire chapter, 2 Corinthians

00:00:07.599 --> 00:00:09.880
9, looking at verses 1 through 15.

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:14.960
This morning, as many of you know, our theme, you see on the banners behind me, God's grace

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:16.719
is sufficient.

00:00:16.719 --> 00:00:22.120
And for those of you that are visiting with us this morning, we are going through on Sunday

00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:25.440
mornings the book of 2 Corinthians.

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:27.639
And it's been our study for Sunday mornings.

00:00:27.639 --> 00:00:33.360
We choose a theme each year, and by God's grace and with God's help, we endeavor to

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:38.360
preach through the particular book or on that topic, that theme subject, throughout the

00:00:38.360 --> 00:00:40.159
calendar year.

00:00:40.159 --> 00:00:43.919
And so this morning, we'll be in 2 Corinthians chapter number 9.

00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:50.040
And our text this morning concludes the section, and I'll call it section on giving, for we

00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:55.979
see in verse 8, or chapters 8 and chapter 9, that there's information given to us with

00:00:55.979 --> 00:01:01.299
regard to giving, the circumstances regarding the collection for the saints, and the example

00:01:01.299 --> 00:01:07.220
of the churches of Macedonia have been highlighted for us in chapter number 8.

00:01:07.220 --> 00:01:13.459
And we find today, as we begin to even touch on the subject of giving, that oftentimes

00:01:13.459 --> 00:01:20.239
the subject of giving within the church is one of those kind of taboo kind of subjects.

00:01:20.239 --> 00:01:22.339
People don't like talking about it.

00:01:22.339 --> 00:01:26.819
And I hope this morning that as we would examine the scriptures, that God would help

00:01:26.819 --> 00:01:27.819
us.

00:01:27.819 --> 00:01:33.739
See, this morning, I believe that in our culture, there's some misunderstandings with regard

00:01:33.739 --> 00:01:35.860
to giving.

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:40.620
There are some that believe that the church just wants your money.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:44.019
It's a thought that some people have.

00:01:44.019 --> 00:01:49.980
There are some that believe that they can gain God's favor through their giving.

00:01:49.980 --> 00:01:54.660
And I would say that both of those are misunderstandings, and I know that there are some places that

00:01:54.660 --> 00:01:59.699
may teach something along those lines, but that's not biblical.

00:01:59.699 --> 00:02:05.239
The concept of giving is a biblical concept, a biblical principle that goes all the way

00:02:05.239 --> 00:02:09.419
back to Genesis chapter 14, as you look at Abraham.

00:02:09.419 --> 00:02:13.899
Begin to find, as you study through the Old Testament, the instruction that was given,

00:02:13.899 --> 00:02:19.500
the instruction to God's people with regard to the subject of giving, even as I taught

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:25.619
the teens in Sunday school this morning, in 2 Chronicles chapter 24, Joash goes to

00:02:25.619 --> 00:02:31.139
Jehoiada and says, hey, why aren't we having them bring the offering as the commandment

00:02:31.139 --> 00:02:34.779
of the Lord by the servant of the Lord Moses?

00:02:34.779 --> 00:02:39.539
And then they begin to bring the offering, and they can repair the house as God had instituted

00:02:39.539 --> 00:02:42.539
for it to be done, and they were fulfilling.

00:02:42.539 --> 00:02:46.259
And here's one of the things that I said to the young people this morning, that God's

00:02:46.259 --> 00:02:50.020
provision is always through God's people.

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:55.380
And I'm thankful for God's provision, I'm thankful, as we begin to think about the subject

00:02:55.380 --> 00:03:00.240
of giving, that the truth regarding giving is that it is one way for us as believers

00:03:00.240 --> 00:03:03.179
to worship and to honor God.

00:03:03.179 --> 00:03:08.360
When we give, it's an act of worship, and we're honoring the Lord, and we're being able

00:03:08.360 --> 00:03:09.619
to participate.

00:03:09.619 --> 00:03:16.020
Why is it that we have a time in our service where we take up an offering, not so that

00:03:16.059 --> 00:03:21.139
the church can get money, it's so that we can worship God through our giving.

00:03:21.139 --> 00:03:23.860
And I am thankful that we have a Bible.

00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:30.460
I want you to think about this this morning, God is the authority on every subject.

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:31.740
Amen?

00:03:31.740 --> 00:03:36.839
And God is the one who has given us a book, the Bible, that is eternal.

00:03:36.839 --> 00:03:38.179
His book is perfect.

00:03:38.179 --> 00:03:42.100
The Bible says of itself that it is profitable for us.

00:03:42.179 --> 00:03:49.419
So it would behoove us not to ignore a subject such as finances, but that we would discover

00:03:49.419 --> 00:03:57.020
through searching God's word, principles for giving and utilizing our finances properly.

00:03:57.020 --> 00:04:03.580
The reality is that there are many today that may visit a financial advisor, and if you've

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:08.660
done that, I'm not against that, I'm simply saying that some would go to a financial advisor

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:14.580
and get some type of financial advice, and oftentimes, as I've heard people even share

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:19.739
this with me, that they've told me I'm crazy because I give to the church, or I shouldn't

00:04:19.739 --> 00:04:26.100
do this, I should do these things first, and we have to understand God's word is the authority.

00:04:26.100 --> 00:04:30.940
And it is absolutely vital that as we come to this text of Scripture this morning, that

00:04:30.940 --> 00:04:36.820
we recognize today that we are blessed to have this passage of Scripture, why?

00:04:36.820 --> 00:04:43.260
Because it enables us to develop a perspective that is biblical with regard to our giving.

00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:46.940
And so this morning as we begin looking here in 2 Corinthians chapter number 9, notice

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:52.980
the Bible says in verse number 1, for it is touching and ministering to the saints, it

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:58.779
is superfluous for me to write to you, for I know the forwardness of your mind for which

00:04:58.779 --> 00:05:05.899
I boast of you to them of Macedonia, that Achaia was ready a year ago, and your zeal

00:05:06.019 --> 00:05:08.619
hath provoked very many.

00:05:08.619 --> 00:05:11.299
Now skip down, if you will, we'll look at the entire chapter, but I want you to skip

00:05:11.299 --> 00:05:16.019
down to verse number 6, the Bible says this, but this I say, he which soweth sparingly

00:05:16.019 --> 00:05:22.100
shall reap also sparingly, and he which soweth bountifully shall reap also bountifully.

00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:27.019
Every man according as he purposeth in his heart, so let him give, not grudgingly or

00:05:27.019 --> 00:05:34.019
of necessity, then notice this phrase, for God loveth a cheerful giver.

00:05:34.739 --> 00:05:40.179
And I've simply titled the message this morning from verse number 7 in our text, God loveth

00:05:40.179 --> 00:05:42.540
a cheerful giver.

00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:45.619
You know, often times, and I even said this to the young people this morning, not within

00:05:45.619 --> 00:05:51.420
regard to the context of giving, but often times I try to share this perspective with

00:05:51.420 --> 00:05:55.700
people, I don't have to, but I get to.

00:05:55.700 --> 00:06:00.579
You know, you didn't have to come to church this morning, no one forced you to be here,

00:06:00.579 --> 00:06:06.619
at least I don't think so, and you weren't forced to be here, but you get to be here.

00:06:06.619 --> 00:06:10.899
And you know, what a privilege it is to be able to assemble with the people of God and

00:06:10.899 --> 00:06:17.299
worship the Lord through song and open up a Bible and study the truth of God's word,

00:06:17.299 --> 00:06:22.779
and to find out what God has for me, what God has for you.

00:06:22.779 --> 00:06:27.079
No one forced you to put something in the offering plate, but if you did, it was because

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:33.160
you had a desire to worship the Lord and to honor the Lord, and we don't have to, but

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:35.320
we get to.

00:06:35.320 --> 00:06:36.679
And can I say this?

00:06:36.679 --> 00:06:44.000
It is always advantageous for the individual to obey the Lord, amen?

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.920
Obedience throughout the scriptures is always met with blessing.

00:06:48.920 --> 00:06:50.839
Disobedience is always met with cursing.

00:06:50.839 --> 00:06:56.839
And we find that throughout the scriptures, it is always best for us to do what God has

00:06:56.880 --> 00:06:59.119
commanded us to do.

00:06:59.119 --> 00:07:03.239
So as we look through this passage of scripture, in verses 1 through 5, if you're taking notes,

00:07:03.239 --> 00:07:07.320
I notice first of all, a priority on giving.

00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:11.760
Oftentimes as you study the Old Testament and you read about the nation of Israel with

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:17.519
regard to their giving, you'll note this word often, firstfruits.

00:07:17.519 --> 00:07:18.519
Firstfruits.

00:07:18.519 --> 00:07:23.000
And you begin to understand the faith that is necessary for the children of Israel when

00:07:23.119 --> 00:07:28.160
God would give those commandments and speak to them about these firstfruits and how they

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:31.920
were to give to the Lord first.

00:07:31.920 --> 00:07:37.040
And the reality is that we find throughout the scripture that there is a priority that

00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:39.640
God gives us on giving.

00:07:39.640 --> 00:07:44.679
As believers, we must understand our position as stewards.

00:07:44.679 --> 00:07:48.720
Can I encourage you this morning that everything that you have and everything that I have,

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:51.079
we are to be stewards of.

00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:52.920
I mentioned this a few months ago.

00:07:52.920 --> 00:07:57.119
I have a little sticky on my desk calendar in my office.

00:07:57.119 --> 00:08:01.720
It was from just a, I think it was the only thing in this particular book that I read

00:08:01.720 --> 00:08:04.279
that I, that was a takeaway for me.

00:08:04.279 --> 00:08:11.440
And that was this, stop trying to possess what God gave you to steward.

00:08:11.440 --> 00:08:16.160
And man, that simple statement just absolutely impacted my heart.

00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:17.160
Why?

00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:19.000
Because we're stewards.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:25.320
We're not just stewards of our time, though we are, and time is fleeting.

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:26.320
What is your life?

00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:30.600
It's a vapor that appears for a little time and then vanisheth away.

00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:35.799
But we also understand that we're stewards of our treasure, of that which God has entrusted

00:08:35.799 --> 00:08:36.799
us with.

00:08:36.799 --> 00:08:40.719
As we go through the message this morning, we'll find that all that we have is because

00:08:40.719 --> 00:08:41.719
of God.

00:08:41.719 --> 00:08:45.919
And we must never forget that, but we find that there's this, this perspective that

00:08:45.919 --> 00:08:49.200
we must have, that we must understand our position.

00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:56.760
And it's imperative that we steward our resources properly so that we are able to honor and

00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:59.919
worship God with our giving.

00:08:59.919 --> 00:09:03.320
You know, there are many things that we can spend our money on.

00:09:03.320 --> 00:09:04.320
Amen?

00:09:04.320 --> 00:09:06.479
I mean, lots of things.

00:09:06.479 --> 00:09:11.140
And listen, when we begin to think about spending our money and our resources, we make decisions,

00:09:11.140 --> 00:09:12.359
we make choices.

00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:18.000
I hope that none of us individually live like our government operates as a nation, because

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:24.380
you can't flourish that way and do those things, and you have to be fiscally responsible.

00:09:24.380 --> 00:09:29.000
As the pastor of our church, I desire not only for me personally and our family, but

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:30.280
also for our church.

00:09:30.280 --> 00:09:34.200
We have budget, and we have budget meetings, and so on and so forth.

00:09:34.200 --> 00:09:35.200
Why?

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:37.200
Because we want to be fiscally responsible.

00:09:37.200 --> 00:09:39.760
And as stewards, that is our responsibility.

00:09:39.760 --> 00:09:42.520
We want to be able to honor and worship the Lord.

00:09:42.520 --> 00:09:46.960
You're bombarded, just as I am all of the time, with the things that we could spend

00:09:46.960 --> 00:09:47.960
our money on.

00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:52.840
Have you ever had remorse after spending money on something?

00:09:52.840 --> 00:09:57.440
You said, man, this thing didn't work the way that it was advertised to work.

00:09:57.440 --> 00:10:00.119
This thing didn't bring the joy to me that

00:10:00.119 --> 00:10:01.679
that it said it was gonna bring to me

00:10:01.679 --> 00:10:03.119
or whatever it might be.

00:10:03.119 --> 00:10:05.599
And we have that buyer's remorse

00:10:05.599 --> 00:10:08.079
as sometimes they'll refer to it.

00:10:08.079 --> 00:10:09.599
But I want you to understand that as we begin

00:10:09.599 --> 00:10:11.599
to understand this priority in giving

00:10:11.599 --> 00:10:13.419
and thinking about giving to God,

00:10:13.419 --> 00:10:15.519
I would say that we note the priority,

00:10:15.519 --> 00:10:18.159
we give to God first, we give God what is right.

00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:20.199
A preacher of yesteryear said it this way,

00:10:20.199 --> 00:10:22.979
give God what is right, not what is left.

00:10:22.979 --> 00:10:26.119
And the reality is that as we look at the text,

00:10:26.119 --> 00:10:28.959
we find that Paul, in these opening verses,

00:10:28.959 --> 00:10:31.879
he's already laid out for them in chapter number eight

00:10:31.879 --> 00:10:34.839
so much with regard to the opportunity to give.

00:10:34.839 --> 00:10:38.159
And he says, for as touching the ministering to the saints,

00:10:38.159 --> 00:10:40.079
this offering that he's speaking about,

00:10:40.079 --> 00:10:42.199
remember at the end of chapter eight,

00:10:42.199 --> 00:10:44.839
he talked about those brothers that were going

00:10:44.839 --> 00:10:48.319
to be entrusted with taking this offering

00:10:48.319 --> 00:10:51.159
and all that they were seeking to accomplish.

00:10:51.159 --> 00:10:54.959
He said, it is superfluous for me to write to you,

00:10:54.959 --> 00:10:58.199
for I know the forwardness of your mind,

00:10:58.199 --> 00:11:00.719
for which I boast of you to them of Macedonia

00:11:00.719 --> 00:11:03.159
that Achaia was ready a year ago,

00:11:03.159 --> 00:11:05.839
and your zeal hath provoked very many.

00:11:05.839 --> 00:11:09.679
Yet have I sent the brethren, lest our boasting of you

00:11:09.679 --> 00:11:12.119
should be in vain in this behalf,

00:11:12.119 --> 00:11:15.239
that as I said, ye may be ready.

00:11:15.239 --> 00:11:18.399
Notice in verse four, lest happily if they of Macedonia

00:11:18.399 --> 00:11:21.759
come with me and find you unprepared,

00:11:21.759 --> 00:11:26.719
we that we say not ye should be ashamed

00:11:26.719 --> 00:11:29.719
in the same confident boasting.

00:11:29.719 --> 00:11:33.079
Therefore, I thought it necessary to exhort the brethren

00:11:33.079 --> 00:11:34.839
that they would go before unto you

00:11:34.839 --> 00:11:37.359
and make up beforehand your bounty,

00:11:37.359 --> 00:11:41.479
whereof ye had noticed before that the same might be ready

00:11:41.479 --> 00:11:45.639
as a matter of bounty and not as of covetousness.

00:11:45.639 --> 00:11:47.399
I want you to notice a few things here.

00:11:47.399 --> 00:11:49.439
He talks about this opportunity.

00:11:49.439 --> 00:11:52.519
He says that you may be ready at the end of verse number three.

00:11:52.519 --> 00:11:55.439
He says there in the midst of verse number four,

00:11:55.439 --> 00:11:58.039
and find you unprepared.

00:11:58.039 --> 00:12:00.119
Now think about that, lack of preparation.

00:12:00.119 --> 00:12:01.719
This is the priority on giving.

00:12:01.719 --> 00:12:04.879
This is the mindset that I'm purposing

00:12:04.879 --> 00:12:07.719
to do what is right before the Lord,

00:12:07.719 --> 00:12:10.360
and I don't wanna be in a place where I'm ill prepared

00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:14.039
or unprepared as the Bible says.

00:12:14.039 --> 00:12:17.479
Man, I wish I would have used my funds different last month

00:12:17.479 --> 00:12:20.759
because I have nothing left over to be able to,

00:12:20.759 --> 00:12:24.000
no, no, we put a priority on it.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:25.519
You know, I've learned this in life

00:12:25.519 --> 00:12:26.759
and I don't know everything.

00:12:26.759 --> 00:12:31.279
I've not lived a full life, only 45 years on this earth,

00:12:31.279 --> 00:12:32.639
but I've learned this.

00:12:32.639 --> 00:12:35.479
If you don't tell your money where it's gonna be spent,

00:12:35.479 --> 00:12:37.459
somehow it gets spent.

00:12:38.599 --> 00:12:40.559
Isn't it pretty interesting how that works?

00:12:40.559 --> 00:12:43.440
And all of a sudden, if you don't have a budget,

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:47.519
you start finding out, man, those coffees,

00:12:47.519 --> 00:12:49.479
that added up to quite a bit.

00:12:49.479 --> 00:12:53.239
I sat in an office with someone about two years ago,

00:12:53.239 --> 00:12:57.159
and I don't know how their finances were personally.

00:12:57.159 --> 00:12:59.679
I did not, it was not my business to ask,

00:12:59.679 --> 00:13:03.399
but he made this comment to me of his own.

00:13:03.399 --> 00:13:06.559
He said to me, I got a baby on the way,

00:13:06.559 --> 00:13:08.679
and I was like, oh, congratulations, that's really exciting.

00:13:08.679 --> 00:13:12.019
He said, we gotta get some things under control though.

00:13:12.019 --> 00:13:17.019
My DoorDash bill for last month was almost $2,000.

00:13:20.720 --> 00:13:22.940
I've never used DoorDash, okay?

00:13:23.539 --> 00:13:25.979
I don't know the fees that are associated with it

00:13:25.979 --> 00:13:28.339
and all of that, but I kind of took a swallow

00:13:28.339 --> 00:13:33.339
and thought, $2,000 in a month on DoorDash?

00:13:34.979 --> 00:13:35.819
You know what happened?

00:13:35.819 --> 00:13:39.220
He had a very busy schedule, and it was very easy

00:13:39.220 --> 00:13:43.619
to just kind of, I'm hungry, I need this, I need whatever.

00:13:43.619 --> 00:13:45.179
What I'm saying to you this morning

00:13:45.179 --> 00:13:48.059
is that there must be a priority on giving,

00:13:48.059 --> 00:13:52.339
that we, as the stewards of God, as the people of God,

00:13:52.339 --> 00:13:54.779
that we have this priority, that we understand,

00:13:54.779 --> 00:13:59.419
I get to give to God, and I'm going to make it a priority.

00:13:59.419 --> 00:14:01.539
Look at the book of Malachi, if you will,

00:14:01.539 --> 00:14:03.179
the last book in the Old Testament,

00:14:03.179 --> 00:14:05.299
Malachi chapter number three,

00:14:05.299 --> 00:14:06.879
and begin to find some things here

00:14:06.879 --> 00:14:08.500
that God is going to give us

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:12.299
with regard to this priority on giving.

00:14:12.299 --> 00:14:14.979
In fact, in other portions of scripture

00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.519
of the Old Testament, God tells his people

00:14:17.519 --> 00:14:20.660
to consider their ways, he tells them about making money

00:14:20.699 --> 00:14:23.260
to put it in bags that have holes,

00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:26.139
and he uses this imagery and these analogies

00:14:26.139 --> 00:14:28.660
to help them understand the principle

00:14:28.660 --> 00:14:30.079
that I mentioned to you a moment ago

00:14:30.079 --> 00:14:33.660
that we see so often in the Old Testament of firstfruits.

00:14:33.660 --> 00:14:35.699
In chapter number three of the book of Malachi,

00:14:35.699 --> 00:14:38.220
in verse number seven, the Bible says this,

00:14:38.220 --> 00:14:40.859
"'Even from the days of your fathers,

00:14:40.859 --> 00:14:44.059
"'you're gone away from mine ordinances

00:14:44.059 --> 00:14:46.639
"'and have not kept them.

00:14:46.639 --> 00:14:49.339
"'Return unto me.'"

00:14:49.339 --> 00:14:50.979
So I'm gonna pause right here

00:14:50.979 --> 00:14:52.940
and help us just for a moment.

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:55.979
God says, I've given you instruction.

00:14:55.979 --> 00:14:58.459
Specifically within this context,

00:14:58.459 --> 00:15:01.059
he's going to begin talking about giving

00:15:01.059 --> 00:15:03.859
and how they were guilty of robbing God,

00:15:03.859 --> 00:15:05.779
and in giving them the instruction,

00:15:05.779 --> 00:15:08.299
he's saying, I've provided you with instruction.

00:15:08.299 --> 00:15:11.940
By the way, if it's God who has provided the instruction,

00:15:11.940 --> 00:15:13.899
is it good instruction?

00:15:13.899 --> 00:15:14.979
Absolutely.

00:15:14.979 --> 00:15:16.820
Is it right instruction?

00:15:16.820 --> 00:15:17.660
Absolutely.

00:15:17.660 --> 00:15:19.820
Is it profitable instruction?

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:20.940
Absolutely.

00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:22.500
You say, but it doesn't make sense to me

00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:25.260
because I could do more if I kept more.

00:15:25.260 --> 00:15:27.679
No, no, God's ways are not our ways,

00:15:27.679 --> 00:15:30.299
and he transcends us,

00:15:30.299 --> 00:15:32.479
and his thoughts are greater than our thoughts,

00:15:32.479 --> 00:15:34.540
and the reality is that he says,

00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:38.339
I've given you truth, but you've gone away.

00:15:39.179 --> 00:15:40.220
So what does he say?

00:15:40.220 --> 00:15:41.739
Return.

00:15:41.739 --> 00:15:43.380
He doesn't say, listen,

00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:46.040
God is not gonna bargain with you or me.

00:15:48.019 --> 00:15:48.859
Let me say that again.

00:15:48.859 --> 00:15:50.419
I don't think you believe it.

00:15:50.419 --> 00:15:53.139
God's not gonna bargain with you or with me.

00:15:53.139 --> 00:15:54.660
I'm not gonna come to a place and say,

00:15:54.660 --> 00:15:56.760
well, God, you know my bills, and you know this,

00:15:56.760 --> 00:15:58.139
and you know I really wanna do this thing,

00:15:58.139 --> 00:16:01.139
and so, God, would you just, no, no, no.

00:16:01.139 --> 00:16:02.699
That's not how it works.

00:16:02.699 --> 00:16:05.899
God doesn't say to these people in Malachi 3,

00:16:05.899 --> 00:16:08.820
I'm gonna give you new instruction.

00:16:08.820 --> 00:16:10.899
You've not obeyed what I've told you,

00:16:10.899 --> 00:16:15.899
so I'm gonna change it up to be more comfortable for you,

00:16:16.779 --> 00:16:19.979
to be more relevant in your time.

00:16:19.979 --> 00:16:21.699
No, he says return.

00:16:22.820 --> 00:16:24.059
He says return.

00:16:24.059 --> 00:16:24.979
I'm not changing.

00:16:24.979 --> 00:16:26.339
You need to change.

00:16:26.339 --> 00:16:27.260
Amend your ways.

00:16:27.260 --> 00:16:28.619
Consider your ways, right?

00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:30.600
Why?

00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:32.899
Because the principle that God gave

00:16:32.899 --> 00:16:37.179
is a principle that is established throughout the time,

00:16:38.220 --> 00:16:40.220
and so here we find that God,

00:16:40.220 --> 00:16:42.179
he's not gonna bargain with these people.

00:16:42.179 --> 00:16:43.899
He's not gonna bargain with you.

00:16:43.899 --> 00:16:45.019
You're not gonna, but God,

00:16:45.779 --> 00:16:46.899
you know the inflation.

00:16:46.899 --> 00:16:48.739
You know the, no, no.

00:16:49.859 --> 00:16:51.220
God says return.

00:16:51.220 --> 00:16:53.419
Notice with me as we continue reading in verse number seven,

00:16:53.419 --> 00:16:55.619
and I will return unto you, saith the Lord of hosts,

00:16:55.619 --> 00:16:58.100
but ye said, wherein shall we return?

00:16:58.100 --> 00:16:59.699
Then notice verse eight.

00:16:59.699 --> 00:17:01.739
Will a man rob God?

00:17:03.260 --> 00:17:05.919
I want you to pause and think about that just for a moment.

00:17:05.919 --> 00:17:09.419
Just reading those words are convicting.

00:17:10.699 --> 00:17:11.619
I would say this.

00:17:11.619 --> 00:17:13.859
Most of us would never use that terminology.

00:17:15.220 --> 00:17:16.859
That we robbed God.

00:17:16.859 --> 00:17:19.720
We don't want to rob anyone, right?

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:22.739
I don't want to be guilty of being a thief.

00:17:22.739 --> 00:17:24.699
I don't want to rob someone,

00:17:24.699 --> 00:17:27.299
let alone God who is the possessor of heaven and earth,

00:17:27.299 --> 00:17:29.619
who's my heavenly father, who loves me,

00:17:29.619 --> 00:17:31.859
who gave me everything that I have.

00:17:31.859 --> 00:17:34.179
I don't want to be guilty of robbing God.

00:17:34.179 --> 00:17:35.660
Think about the nation of Israel

00:17:35.660 --> 00:17:36.940
that's being spoken to here

00:17:36.940 --> 00:17:39.579
in all of the manifold blessings

00:17:39.579 --> 00:17:41.660
that God had bestowed upon them,

00:17:41.660 --> 00:17:44.059
and he says, will a man rob God?

00:17:44.059 --> 00:17:47.320
Yet ye have robbed me.

00:17:47.320 --> 00:17:50.899
But ye say, wherein have we robbed thee?

00:17:50.899 --> 00:17:54.739
In tithes and offerings.

00:17:54.739 --> 00:17:55.579
Then he says this.

00:17:55.579 --> 00:17:58.059
Ye are cursed with a curse,

00:17:58.059 --> 00:18:02.859
for ye have robbed me, even this whole nation.

00:18:02.859 --> 00:18:07.859
Oftentimes when I've had the opportunity

00:18:07.899 --> 00:18:10.940
to sit down and to counsel with folks,

00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:13.299
and sometimes the counsel is varied

00:18:13.339 --> 00:18:14.500
with regard to the subjects,

00:18:14.500 --> 00:18:16.699
but every once in a while there's counseling

00:18:16.699 --> 00:18:18.419
that comes up that's financial.

00:18:18.419 --> 00:18:21.339
I'm not a financial advisor in any way, shape, or form.

00:18:21.339 --> 00:18:25.179
You don't want my advice on making investments

00:18:25.179 --> 00:18:26.220
and all that sort of thing,

00:18:26.220 --> 00:18:28.299
but there are people that will come and ask me

00:18:28.299 --> 00:18:30.179
when they got some financial hardships

00:18:30.179 --> 00:18:32.140
and so on and so forth.

00:18:32.140 --> 00:18:36.739
And every time I start the conversation this way.

00:18:36.739 --> 00:18:37.760
How's your tithing?

00:18:40.779 --> 00:18:42.419
And almost every single time,

00:18:42.419 --> 00:18:43.979
you know what the response is?

00:18:43.979 --> 00:18:46.539
This has nothing to do with that.

00:18:46.539 --> 00:18:50.299
And I say this, it has everything to do with that.

00:18:51.219 --> 00:18:54.679
It has everything to do with that.

00:18:54.679 --> 00:18:57.979
Now again, let me help us this morning

00:18:57.979 --> 00:18:59.700
not have the walls up.

00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:01.460
The preacher's talking about money.

00:19:01.460 --> 00:19:03.419
No, no, God's talking about money.

00:19:04.700 --> 00:19:08.099
God is the authority in every area of our lives,

00:19:08.099 --> 00:19:09.979
including our finances.

00:19:09.979 --> 00:19:13.500
Some people will pay to go to a financial advisor

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:15.900
to get their advice on how to use their money

00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:18.179
while never going to the Bible

00:19:18.179 --> 00:19:21.700
to get the truth that God provides for them

00:19:21.700 --> 00:19:24.219
with regard to finances.

00:19:24.219 --> 00:19:26.580
And so God says you're cursed with a curse.

00:19:26.580 --> 00:19:27.419
Why?

00:19:27.419 --> 00:19:28.299
Because you've robbed me.

00:19:28.299 --> 00:19:29.279
Robbed me how?

00:19:29.279 --> 00:19:31.059
With tithes and offerings.

00:19:31.900 --> 00:19:33.820
Well, I put a little bit in.

00:19:33.820 --> 00:19:36.099
A tithe is really easy to calculate.

00:19:37.140 --> 00:19:39.179
It's not complicated.

00:19:39.179 --> 00:19:41.859
And the reality is that God then says this

00:19:41.859 --> 00:19:44.739
to the nation of Israel in Malachi 3 and verse 10.

00:19:45.659 --> 00:19:50.659
Bring ye all the tithes into the storehouse.

00:19:51.339 --> 00:19:55.400
Then notice that there may be meat in mine house

00:19:55.400 --> 00:20:00.400
and prove me now herewith, saith the Lord of hosts.

00:20:00.400 --> 00:20:04.700
If I will not open you the windows of heaven

00:20:04.700 --> 00:20:06.700
and pour you out a blessing,

00:20:06.700 --> 00:20:09.200
that there shall not be room enough to receive it,

00:20:09.200 --> 00:20:12.700
and I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes.

00:20:12.700 --> 00:20:15.200
And he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground,

00:20:15.200 --> 00:20:17.200
neither shall your vine cast her fruit

00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:19.000
before the time in the field,

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.500
saith the Lord of hosts."

00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:24.200
Now, let me be careful to let you know in verses 10 and 11,

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:26.700
this is not prosperity preaching.

00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:29.200
This is not if you give to God, you're gonna get all of this.

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:31.500
No, no, these are principles that God says,

00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:33.000
listen, I'll take care of you.

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:37.000
And he says, prove me now.

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:41.300
You know, it's amazing when God, the creator,

00:20:41.300 --> 00:20:43.300
the one who said, let there be light,

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:46.700
and there was light, that he says to his people,

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:50.500
prove me if I will not do this.

00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:54.000
If you honor me, I'll take care of you.

00:20:55.400 --> 00:20:56.700
I'll take care of you.

00:20:56.800 --> 00:20:59.400
Now, understand with me that God taking care of us

00:20:59.400 --> 00:21:02.000
might not mean that you have a brand new car in the driveway

00:21:02.000 --> 00:21:05.400
and you live in a 7,000 square foot house

00:21:05.400 --> 00:21:06.900
and all this kind of, no, no, that might,

00:21:06.900 --> 00:21:09.000
but God's gonna take care of your needs.

00:21:10.100 --> 00:21:12.500
He's gonna take care of your needs.

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:14.600
But seek ye first the kingdom of God.

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:17.500
Amen, Matthew.

00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:19.300
He says, all these things shall be added unto you.

00:21:19.300 --> 00:21:21.800
He says, don't think about the food,

00:21:21.800 --> 00:21:23.300
the raiment, the shelter.

00:21:23.300 --> 00:21:26.100
God knows that you have need of these things.

00:21:26.100 --> 00:21:27.400
Can I tell you, in America today,

00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:29.800
we're extremely prosperous.

00:21:31.100 --> 00:21:33.800
We're like the Revelation 3,

00:21:33.800 --> 00:21:35.200
the church of the Laodiceans

00:21:35.200 --> 00:21:36.700
that were increased with goods.

00:21:36.700 --> 00:21:39.600
In America, listen, I understand some of the inflation.

00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:41.400
I deal with it the same way you deal with it.

00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.300
I understand all of those things that are going on.

00:21:43.300 --> 00:21:46.800
But at the end of the day, we are still blessed.

00:21:46.800 --> 00:21:48.300
We are so blessed.

00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:52.400
And God says, here's what I'm gonna do.

00:21:52.400 --> 00:21:54.300
He says, prove me now.

00:21:54.300 --> 00:21:55.900
Herewith saith the Lord of hosts,

00:21:55.900 --> 00:21:58.500
if I will not open you the windows of heaven

00:21:58.500 --> 00:22:00.200
and pour you out a blessing

00:22:00.200 --> 00:22:01.900
that there shall not be room enough to receive it.

00:22:01.900 --> 00:22:05.000
Verse 11, not only will God take care of your needs,

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:08.100
but he says, and I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes.

00:22:08.100 --> 00:22:10.800
He shall not destroy the fruits of your ground,

00:22:10.800 --> 00:22:12.900
neither shall your vine cast her fruit

00:22:12.900 --> 00:22:15.500
before the time in the field, saith the Lord of hosts.

00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:17.200
The children of Israel,

00:22:17.200 --> 00:22:20.100
if you look back in that wandering time

00:22:20.100 --> 00:22:23.000
after they were released from Egyptian bondage,

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:25.500
they walked and God had provided them

00:22:25.500 --> 00:22:27.700
with the food that was necessary.

00:22:27.700 --> 00:22:30.200
But the Bible talks about how their shoes,

00:22:30.200 --> 00:22:32.000
their sandals, they didn't wear out

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:35.200
and how God took care of them.

00:22:35.200 --> 00:22:37.000
You know, there are certain times in your life

00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:39.000
and if we'd sit back and evaluate it

00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:41.600
that sometimes God, because we honor him,

00:22:41.600 --> 00:22:44.400
because we put a priority on giving,

00:22:44.400 --> 00:22:47.000
God might let your tires last a little bit longer.

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.000
And you say, pastor, that's ridiculous.

00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:50.700
That's how God can work.

00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:53.700
That's how God can work.

00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:58.000
And this morning, as we look at the truth

00:22:58.000 --> 00:22:59.800
in 2 Corinthians chapter nine,

00:22:59.800 --> 00:23:01.400
the people in Corinth,

00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:04.200
they had to place a priority on giving.

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:06.200
It wasn't something that they'll get around to

00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:07.100
at some point.

00:23:07.100 --> 00:23:08.600
It wasn't something that, well,

00:23:08.600 --> 00:23:10.600
if we have enough, then we will.

00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:13.500
No, God is telling the believers in Corinth

00:23:13.500 --> 00:23:15.300
they need to have a priority.

00:23:15.300 --> 00:23:16.500
And for us this morning,

00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:19.600
there must be a priority on giving.

00:23:19.600 --> 00:23:21.200
I used to say this,

00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:23.600
and now we live in an electronic banking world

00:23:23.600 --> 00:23:25.200
that we don't write a whole lot of checks,

00:23:25.200 --> 00:23:26.600
but I used to say this,

00:23:26.600 --> 00:23:28.900
the first check that I write every week

00:23:28.900 --> 00:23:31.000
or every month is my tithe check.

00:23:31.900 --> 00:23:34.300
So I only get paid once a month

00:23:34.300 --> 00:23:37.600
and now almost the only check I write a month

00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:38.600
is my tithe check

00:23:38.600 --> 00:23:41.500
because almost everything else is electronic.

00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:44.500
But the reality is that there's a priority.

00:23:45.600 --> 00:23:48.300
Why? Because I want to worship God.

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:49.800
I want to honor God.

00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:52.400
Notice as we continue in 2 Corinthians chapter nine,

00:23:52.400 --> 00:23:54.900
I know not only a priority on giving,

00:23:54.900 --> 00:23:58.000
but I see some principles for giving.

00:23:58.000 --> 00:23:59.300
In verses six and seven,

00:23:59.300 --> 00:24:01.000
we read these verses a moment ago

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:02.000
by way of introduction,

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:04.500
but we see some principles that God gives us.

00:24:04.500 --> 00:24:06.600
In verse six, we see this contrast

00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:07.600
where God says,

00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:09.500
he would soweth sparingly,

00:24:09.500 --> 00:24:10.800
shall reap also sparingly,

00:24:10.800 --> 00:24:13.000
and he would soweth bountifully,

00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:14.800
shall reap also bountifully.

00:24:14.800 --> 00:24:15.900
Now it's kind of interesting

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:18.800
that throughout the word of God,

00:24:18.800 --> 00:24:22.200
there's regular analogies or illustrations

00:24:22.200 --> 00:24:23.900
that God uses.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:27.000
Many times agricultural references

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:28.600
are repeated through the Bible.

00:24:28.600 --> 00:24:31.900
Why? Because they were an agricultural people.

00:24:31.900 --> 00:24:32.700
And so therefore,

00:24:32.700 --> 00:24:34.800
they could relate very easily

00:24:34.800 --> 00:24:36.800
with these analogies

00:24:36.800 --> 00:24:38.800
that God would use in his word.

00:24:38.800 --> 00:24:41.500
And so you think about this sowing,

00:24:41.500 --> 00:24:42.600
putting seed in the ground.

00:24:42.600 --> 00:24:45.600
If you sow sparingly

00:24:45.600 --> 00:24:49.200
versus sowing bountifully, right?

00:24:49.200 --> 00:24:52.100
If you just have one tomato plant,

00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:53.100
you're going to get whatever

00:24:53.100 --> 00:24:55.500
a single tomato plant will yield.

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:56.500
But if you're like us

00:24:56.500 --> 00:24:58.100
and you plant six tomato plants,

00:24:58.100 --> 00:25:00.800
you get tomatoes coming out of your ears.

00:25:00.800 --> 00:25:03.900
And the reality is that we understand

00:25:03.900 --> 00:25:05.400
some of those principles

00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:08.800
of sowing and reaping physically.

00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:12.500
But here, the application is put on

00:25:12.500 --> 00:25:16.600
with regard to giving, giving.

00:25:16.600 --> 00:25:17.700
I've often said this,

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:19.300
the Bible says in verse number seven,

00:25:19.300 --> 00:25:21.300
you begin to look at this truth.

00:25:21.300 --> 00:25:23.000
And I've often said that

00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:25.400
the tithe is a starting point.

00:25:25.400 --> 00:25:27.500
The Bible says tithes and offerings.

00:25:27.500 --> 00:25:29.000
We have a missions program

00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:30.100
that we give to missions.

00:25:30.100 --> 00:25:31.600
Here, contextually,

00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:33.300
in 2 Corinthians 8 and 9,

00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:35.400
it's really not dealing with tithes

00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:37.900
as much as it's dealing with a love offering

00:25:37.900 --> 00:25:41.200
for a specific need for the brethren.

00:25:41.200 --> 00:25:42.900
And so we find that here

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:43.900
in verse number seven,

00:25:43.900 --> 00:25:45.000
every man according

00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:48.100
as he purposeth in his heart,

00:25:48.100 --> 00:25:50.800
so let him give.

00:25:50.800 --> 00:25:54.700
Not grudgingly or of necessity,

00:25:54.700 --> 00:25:58.900
for God loveth a cheerful giver.

00:25:58.900 --> 00:26:00.500
Now think about the principles here,

00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:01.700
those principles in verse six

00:26:01.700 --> 00:26:03.700
of sparingly and bountifully

00:26:03.700 --> 00:26:06.500
and how we could apply that to our giving.

00:26:06.500 --> 00:26:07.500
But then we also notice

00:26:07.500 --> 00:26:10.900
that it says as he purposeth in his heart.

00:26:10.900 --> 00:26:13.200
How much time do we really give

00:26:13.200 --> 00:26:15.300
to seeking the Lord

00:26:15.300 --> 00:26:18.100
with regard to our giving?

00:26:18.100 --> 00:26:20.600
How much time do we consider,

00:26:20.600 --> 00:26:21.900
Lord, what would you like me to do?

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:23.200
We just had a revival meeting.

00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:24.400
As a church,

00:26:24.400 --> 00:26:28.900
we don't often have a lot of special offerings.

00:26:28.900 --> 00:26:30.200
We have a special offering

00:26:30.200 --> 00:26:31.700
typically during missions conference

00:26:31.700 --> 00:26:33.100
and during revival meeting

00:26:33.100 --> 00:26:35.300
and maybe another time during the year

00:26:35.300 --> 00:26:37.000
we have a missions Christmas offering

00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:38.300
that we do.

00:26:38.300 --> 00:26:39.100
But other than that,

00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:41.000
not too many special offerings.

00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.000
But I've encouraged you this calendar year,

00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:44.300
both with the missions conference

00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:45.700
and the revival meeting,

00:26:45.700 --> 00:26:49.200
ask God what he would have you give.

00:26:49.200 --> 00:26:49.900
We seek God.

00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:52.700
He says as he purposeth in his heart.

00:26:52.700 --> 00:26:53.200
And then it says,

00:26:53.200 --> 00:26:56.500
so let him give not grudgingly

00:26:56.500 --> 00:26:59.400
or of necessity

00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:02.200
for God loveth a cheerful giver.

00:27:02.200 --> 00:27:04.600
This is that idea where I mentioned earlier

00:27:04.600 --> 00:27:06.200
that we get to give to God.

00:27:06.200 --> 00:27:07.300
I don't have to,

